snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin listClusters Sample
snippets.description: Lists Clusters in a given project and location.

snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin getCluster Sample
snippets.description: Gets details of a single Cluster.

snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin createCluster Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new Cluster in a given project and location.

snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin updateCluster Sample
snippets.description: Updates the parameters of a single Cluster.

snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin upgradeCluster Sample
snippets.description: Upgrades a single Cluster. Imperative only.

snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin deleteCluster Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a single Cluster.

snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin promoteCluster Sample
snippets.description: Promotes a SECONDARY cluster. This turns down replication from the PRIMARY cluster and promotes a secondary cluster into its own standalone cluster. Imperative only.

snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin switchoverCluster Sample
snippets.description: Switches the roles of PRIMARY and SECONDARY clusters without any data loss. This promotes the SECONDARY cluster to PRIMARY and sets up the original PRIMARY cluster to replicate from this newly promoted cluster.

snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin restoreCluster Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new Cluster in a given project and location, with a volume restored from the provided source, either a backup ID or a point-in-time and a source cluster.

snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin createSecondaryCluster Sample
snippets.description: Creates a cluster of type SECONDARY in the given location using the primary cluster as the source.

snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin getInstance Sample
snippets.description: Gets details of a single Instance.

snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin createInstance Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new Instance in a given project and location.

snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin createSecondaryInstance Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new SECONDARY Instance in a given project and location.

snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin batchCreateInstances Sample
snippets.description: Creates new instances under the given project, location and cluster. There can be only one primary instance in a cluster. If the primary instance exists in the cluster as well as this request, then API will throw an error. The primary instance should exist before any read pool instance is created. If the primary instance is a part of the request payload, then the API will take care of creating instances in the correct order. This method is here to support Google-internal use cases, and is not meant for external customers to consume. Please do not start relying on it; its behavior is subject to change without notice.

snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin deleteInstance Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a single Instance.

snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin failoverInstance Sample
snippets.description: Forces a Failover for a highly available instance. Failover promotes the HA standby instance as the new primary. Imperative only.

snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin injectFault Sample
snippets.description: Injects fault in an instance. Imperative only.

snippets.title: AlloyDBAdmin restartInstance Sample
snippets.description: Restart an Instance in a cluster. Imperative only.

The endpoint's behavior is subject to change without notice, so do not rely on its behavior remaining constant. Future changes will not break AlloyDB connectors or the Auth Proxy client.
